A phase I or II test is performed prior to safety tests and immunogenicity, usually randomized, is controlled by placebo and is performed on several sites, while determining more accurate and effective doses.
Phase III trials usually involve more participants, including a control group, and evaluate the effectiveness of the vaccine to prevent the disease while controlling the adverse effects that occur with the optimal dose.
