Some medical procedures, such as intubation and cardiopulmonary respiration (RCP) may cause aerosolisation of respiratory secretions and consequently air transmission.
Although there are concerns about the possibility of spreading by insects, the risk is believed to be low. The virus is more contagious when people have symptoms; although the spread is possible before the onset of symptoms, the risk is low.
